// STRESS 11: edge cases in function bodies
// edges: function inside function, calling from main with many args,
//        function returning early, function with no body
Create a console application.

Make a function called outer(int x) that returns an int:
    set y = x * 2
    return y

Make a function called silent() that returns an int.

When the program starts:
    call outer(5)
    call silent
    call outer(10)
    print "done"
